{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (0 blocking, 1 advisory). Triage — advisory [E6,F1] valid: the run-log ACs (AC2-AC5) lack a described evidence-generation procedure. Remediation — I will define + execute the concrete procedure:\n- AC2 (feature/* triggers CI): create feature/s3-ci branch, push a trivial change to refs/for/refs/heads/feature/s3-ci, observe the GitHub Actions run dispatched by g2p (patchset-created -> gerrit-verify.yaml) and the Verified vote it casts.\n- AC3 (merge change gets CI on merge tree): push a --no-ff merge change to refs/for/main, confirm the checkout-gerrit-change-action fetched the MERGE refspec and CI built the merge tree.\n- AC4 (Verified re-runs, no carry): land an unrelated change on main mid-flight, re-merge (MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE), confirm Verified RE-RUNS (fresh run id), not carried.\n- AC5 (concurrency): trigger concurrent branch + merge changes, document concurrency: cancel-in-progress behavior with a run example.\n- AC1 (branch filtering): read g2p source/gerrit_to_platform.ini spec to record a VERIFIED statement (config or no-op) with citation. Starting there."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783060512698617001,"uuid":"33eec6c9-16a1-4ee5-9996-c44cc097c7a4"}